        "title": "Constitutional Bench clarifies the test on equal pay for equal work",
        "excerpt": "<p>The Supreme Court's five-judge bench has, in a rare unanimous ruling, redrawn the contours of Article 39(d). Here's what changes for public-sector employers and the government's salary review mechanism.</p>",
        "content": "<p>The Court's order, running to 187 pages, settles a question that has divided High Courts for over a decade. Section 16 of the Industrial Disputes Act was read down for narrow application.</p><h2>What the bench decided</h2><p>Article 39(d) is a directive principle, but the Court held it informs the equality guarantee under Article 14 and Article 16. The test articulated in <span class=\"citation\">AIR 1973 SC 1461</span> stands modified.</p>",
        "date": "2025-04-22T09:30:00",
        "modified": "2025-04-22T11:15:00",
        "featuredImage": {
          "node": {
            "sourceUrl": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589994965851-a8f479c573a9?w=1600",
            "altText": "Supreme Court of India facade at dusk"
          }
        },
        "author": {
          "node": {
            "name": "Aanya Mehra",
            "slug": "aanya-mehra",
            "description": "Aanya covers the Supreme Court for Insight Lawyer.",
            "avatar": { "url": "https://i.pravatar.cc/120?u=aanya" },
            "roles": { "nodes": [{ "displayName": "Senior Reporter", "name": "author" }] }
          }
        },
